{
  "texts": [
    "In order to simulate queries, we proceed as follows: Choose a query treatment -which belongs to an MoA or pathway that has at least two treatments in the database and, therefore, it is possible to find a match.",
    "Library treatments -all the others while leaving the query treatment out.",
    "Library treatments represent a database of treatments with known MoAs or pathways annotations, which can be candidate matches for a given query.",
    "For each query treatment we calculate the odds ratio of a one-sided Fisher's exact test.",
    "The test is calculated using a 2 × 2 contingency table: the first row contains a number of treatments with the same MoAs or pathways (positive matches) and different MoAs or pathways (negative matches) at a selected threshold of the list of results."
  ]
}